id: concept_compartmentalization
name: Compartmentalization
type: pattern
status: canonical
version: "0.1"

summary: >
  Selective partitioning of awareness and processing load to preserve function under stress.
  A limited-bandwidth system actively suppresses lower-priority signals to protect
  higher-priority operations from degradation.

core_invariant: >
  Limited bandwidth systems preserve function by deferring or suppressing lower-priority
  signals without destroying them.

compression_phrase: "Seal the flooded chamber, keep the vessel moving."

domains:
  - cognition
  - survival
  - control-systems
  - ai-governance
  - military-operations

neighbors:
  - concept_attention_gating
  - concept_predictive_processing
  - concept_pain_modulation
  - concept_reversibility_gate
  - concept_recovery_window
  - concept_mission_priority_filter

failure_modes:
  - chronic suppression — deferred signals never processed, damage accumulates invisibly
  - hidden damage accumulation — system appears functional while degrading
  - delayed emotional or signal rebound — suppressed load resurfaces at wrong moment
  - permanent mode adoption — temporary measure becomes structural, reversibility lost
  - false confidence — operator reads stability as health

transfers:
  - cognition_to_ai_attention
  - pain_signal_to_error_budget
  - military_compartmentalization_to_agent_routing

safety_constraints:
  - suppression must be reversible
  - deferred signals require a defined later-processing window
  - do not use as permanent operating mode
  - operator must be able to inspect suppressed signal queue

aliases:
  - selective partitioning
  - watertight bulkheads
